reviewText: I'm an ICARLY fan and it gets better and better. Can't wait for next season. Would recomend it for youth of all ages.

The previous episodes of this show are much better, but this is still pretty good.

iSam's Mom: B-
iGet Pranky: B+
iSell Penny Tees: B
iDo: C+
iStart a Fan War: C
iHire an Idiot: A
iPity the Nevel: A
iOMG: D-
iParty with Victorious: B+

There are 12 episodes in this season...if you havn't noticed,iParty with victorious is 3 episodes. The air time was back to back,so it might of confused alot of idiots. Season 4 however is not finished...but the sad news is that the reason for the hold off on airing them is because season 4 is the final and last season of icarly..but be looking forward for more episodes in the spring featuring:(michelle Obama) as a special guest,and a few more suprises!

sincerely,

DavinCross

Before buying this make sure you know what it contains, it has episode of season 4 not 3 so DO NOT be confused with 3,for some odd reason they put season 3 on iCarly season 2, Volume 3.  So there you go if you want 4 get the 3rd season if you want the 3rd season get the iCarly season 2, Volume 3 just a heads up Volume 3 doesn't include iThink They Kissed and iCook their actually in iCarly season 2, Volume 2.  Hope this helps.

I bought this and the ICarly season two, volume two for my twin girls age 8.  Since we cut our cable bill they do not watch much tv.  It is really nice to for them to just pop in the dvd and watch their shows.  Both dvd's have lots of their favoriate shows.  It's definitely worth the money!

Disc 1
iGot a Hot Room  4 Stars
iDo- Meh. 3 Stars
iSell Penny Tees- Jennette was Funny- 5 Stars
iGet Pranky- Funny. 4 Stars
iSam's Mom- Loved Jane Lynch. 5 Stars
iPity the Nevel- OK. 3 Stars

Disc 2
iHire an Idiot- Meh- 2.5 Stars
iStart a Fan War- 5 Stars, Seddie/ Creddie Setup
iOMG (Season 4 not 3)- The Must See Episode On The Disc- Seddie Begins
iParty with Victorious (Season 4 not 3)- 4 Stars

Some real gems but if you just watched them, you will not see anything new. However, for a hardcore fan, this is a much for the Seddie/Creddie stuff alone.

I bought this for a friends daughter for her birthday. She is to young to really write any reviews, but I can. All I can say, is if this is truely a full season set, something is seriously wrong with film company or they "Falsely Advertised" a sell. From what I have been able to gather about this show, the last 2 episodes are not even Season 3 but are from Season 4 and the last one (iParty) is not even a complete issue as filmed. It is cut and chopped, but when I read other reviews on here about this orginazation and the way they put out DVD I am not so suprised. Be warned when buying anything for anyone from [...] and its kids shows. What a rip-off!

My son watches this show, so that means I have to watch the show. From the other nickelodeon shows he watches this one really isn't to different. Three kids have a web show that leads them to improbable situations. You can jump into any season on any episode to begin watching the series. There is no deep plots or really any life lessons to be learned. I give it three stars because it keeps my kid occupied, doesn't give kids any wrong impressions, and is overall the production quality seems pretty solid. It just doesn't stand out against any of the other shows children have access to these days.

iCarly is a cute show.  Honestly -- as a mom -- the only things that occasionally bother me are
1) the blatant disrespect of adults and
2) boy/girl relationships that are occasionally over-done.

Overall, we enjoy the show as a family.  Personally, Spenser is my fave.  He cracks me up.
